template.name: Template Redis Server
template.description:
This template should be applied to any servers that host the Redis application server.
The data items within this template require the Zabbix module "libabxredis" to be installed and configured on the Zabbix agent.

item.name: Redis Server - Port Connection Duration
item.description:
This items contains the length of time in seconds it takes to connect to the Redis server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Server - Port Connection Status
item.description:
This items contains the status of the Redis server port used to connect.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Used System Cpu
item.description: This items contains the cpu system usage of the redis server process.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Used Cpu
item.description: This items contains the cpu total usage of the redis server process.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Used User Cpu
item.description: This items contains the cpu user usage of the redis server process.

item.name: Redis Memory - Used Virtual Memory
item.description: This items contains the maximum virtual memory usage of the redis server process.

item.name: Redis Server - Process Count (redis-server)
item.description: This items contains the number of redis server processes.

item.name: Redis Commands - Duration (PING)
item.description: This items contains the time in seconds it takes to complete a redis command.

item.name: Redis Commands - Supported (PING)
item.description: This items contains whether the Redis command is supported.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Consumed System Cpu (Seconds)
item.description:
This items contains the consumed system cpu of the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Consumed System Cpu Background Proceses (Seconds)
item.description:
This items contains the used cpu (sys) children percentage of the Redis application server expressed in seconds.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Consumed User Cpu (Seconds)
item.description:
This items contains the consumed user cpu of the Redis application server expressed in seconds.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Cpu - Consumed User Cpu Background Proceses (Seconds)
item.description:

For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Memory - Memory Fragmentation Ratio
item.description:
This items contains the ratio between used rss memory and used memory of the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - AOF Current Rewrite Time Duration
item.description:
This items contains the duration of the on-going AOF rewrite operation if any in seconds.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - AOF Last Rewrite Time Duration
item.description:
This items contains the duration of the last AOF rewrite operation in seconds.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - RDB Current Save Time Duration
item.description:

For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - RDB Last Save Time Duration
item.description:
This items contains the duration of the last RDB save operation in seconds.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Stats - Instantaneous Input Bytes Per/Sec
item.description:
This items contains the instantaneous input bytes per second by the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Stats - Instantaneous Output Bytes Per/Sec
item.description:
This items contains the instantaneous output bytes per second by the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Clients - Blocked Clients
item.description:
This items contains the number of clients pending on a blocking call.

item.description:

For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Memory - Used Memory LUA Engine
item.description:

For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Memory - Used Memory Peak
item.description:
This items contains the peak memory used by the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Memory - Used Memory RSS
item.description:
This items contains the resident set size memory used by the Redis application server.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - AOF Enabled
item.description:
This items contains a flag indicating AOF logging is activated.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - AOF Rewrite In Progress
item.description:
This items contains a flag indicating a AOF rewrite operation is on-going.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - AOF Rewrite Scheduled
item.description:
This items contains a flag indicating an AOF rewrite operation will be scheduled once the on-going RDB save is complete.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - Dump Loading Flag
item.description:
This items contains a flag indicating if the load of a dump file is on-going.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - RDB Save Flag
item.description:
This items contains a flag indicating a RDB save is on-going.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - RDB Changes Since Last Save
item.description:
This item contains the number of changes since the last save.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Persistence - RDB Last Save Time
item.description:
This items contains the epoch-based time stamp of the last successful RDB save.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item.name: Redis Replication - Slaves Connected
item.description:

item.name: Redis Replication - Master Last IO Time

item.name: Redis Replication - Role
item.description:
This items contains the replication role of the Redis application server.
Value is "master" if the instance is slave of no one, or "slave" if the instance is enslaved to a master. Note that a slave can be master of another slave (daisy chaining).
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

discovery_rule.name: Redis Client Discovery
discovery_rule.description:
This discovery will discover all Redis clients.
The discovered items will be removed instantly when they are not discovered because of the potential high frequency of client connections.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Commands in Multi/Exec context ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the number of commands in MULTI/EXEC context of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Age ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the age in seconds of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Database ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the current database id of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - File Descriptor ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the file descriptor corresponding to the socket of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Identification ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains an unique 64-bit client ID of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Idle ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the idle time seconds of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Output Buffer Length ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the output buffer length of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Output List Length ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the output list length of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Output Buffer Memory Usage ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the output buffer memory usage of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Pattern Matching Subscriptions ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the number of pattern matching subscriptions of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Query Buffer Length ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the query buffer length of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Query Buffer Free ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the query buffer free of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Channel Subscriptions ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the number of channel subscriptions of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Address ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the ip address and port of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Command ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the last command played of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Events ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the file descriptor events of the client connection.
The file descriptor events can be:
r: the client socket is readable (event loop) w: the client socket is writable (event loop)
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Flags ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the flags of the client connection.
The client flags can be a combination of:
O: the client is a slave in MONITOR mode S: the client is a normal slave server M: the client is a master x: the client is in a MULTI/EXEC context b: the client is waiting in a blocking operation i: the client is waiting for a VM I/O (deprecated) d: a watched keys has been modified - EXEC will fail c: connection to be closed after writing entire reply u: the client is unblocked U: the client is connected via a Unix domain socket r: the client is in readonly mode against a cluster node A: connection to be closed ASAP N: no specific flag set
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.name: Redis Client - Name ({#CLIENT})
item_prototype.description:
This item contains the name of the client connection.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

item_prototype.description:

item_prototype.name: Redis Database - Keys To Expire (#{#DATABASE})

item_prototype.name: Redis Database - Keys Defined (#{#DATABASE})
item_prototype.description:
This items contains the number of keys defined within the Redis database.
For further information please see the online Redis documentation located at http://redis.io/documentation.

trigger_prototype.expression: {TRIGGER.VALUE}=0 and ({Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,replication,master_repl_offset,].min(10m)} > {Template Redis Server:redis.slave.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,{#SLAVE},offset,].last()}) or {TRIGGER.VALUE}=1 and ({Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,replication,master_repl_offset,].min(10m)} > {Template Redis Server:redis.slave.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,{#SLAVE},offset,].last()})
trigger_prototype.name: Redis slave {#SLAVE} replication offset has fallen behind master offset for 10 minutes [MASTER={ITEM.VALUE1} SLAVE={ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger_prototype.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis slave offset has fallen behind the master offset for 5 minutes and will return to normal when the Redis slave offset has caught up with the master offset for 5 minutes.

trigger.name: Redis AOF current rewrite duration excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_HIGH}s]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis AOF current rewrite duration is more than {$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_HIGH} seconds and return to normal when the Redis AOF current rewrite duration is less than {$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_OK} seconds.

trigger.name: Redis AOF last rewrite duration excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_HIGH}s]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis AOF last rewrite duration is more than {$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_HIGH} seconds and return to normal when the Redis AOF last rewrite duration is less than {$REDIS_AOF_REWRITE_DURATION_OK} seconds.

trigger.name: Redis AOF last rewrite was not ok on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis AOF last rewrite status is not ok and return to normal when the Redis AOF last rewrite status is ok for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis AOF last write was not ok on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis AOF last write status is not ok and return to normal when the Redis AOF last write status is ok for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis AOF rewrite is scheduled and has not occurred on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis AOF is scheduled and has not occurred for more than {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and return to normal when the Redis AOF is not scheduled for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.expression: ({TRIGGER.VALUE}=0 and (({Template Redis Server:redis.config[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,maxclients,].last()} - {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,clients,connected_clients,].last()})<{$REDIS_CLIENT_FREE})) or ({TRIGGER.VALUE}=1 and (({Template Redis Server:redis.config[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,maxclients,].last()} - {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,clients,connected_clients,].max({$REDIS_OK_TIME})})<{$REDIS_CLIENT_FREE}))
trigger.name: Redis client available connections too low on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE2} Threshold:{$REDIS_CLIENT_FREE}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the counter has less than {$REDIS_CLIENT_FREE} client connections free and will return to normal when the counter has more than {$REDIS_CLIENT_FREE} client connections free for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis client connections blocked increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis connections blocked has increased and will return to normal when the Redis connections blocked remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis client connections rejected increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis connections rejected has increased and will return to normal when the Redis connections rejected remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis client used connections too low on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_CLIENT_MINIMUM}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the counter has less than {$REDIS_CLIENT_MINIMUM} client connections and will return to normal when the counter has more than {$REDIS_CLIENT_MINIMUM} client connections for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis command latency excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} - PING - [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_CMD_LATENCY_HIGH}s]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis ping command latency is greater than {$REDIS_CMD_LATENCY_HIGH} for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis ping command latency is less than {$REDIS_CMD_LATENCY_OK} for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis configuration error on {$REDIS_SERVER} repl-timeout [{ITEM.VALUE1}] should be greater than repl-ping-slave-period [{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description:
This trigger will fire when there is a Redis configuration error detected.
According to the configuration file documentation it is important to make sure that repl-timeout is greater than repl-ping-slave-period otherwise a timeout will be detected every time there is low traffic between the master and the slave.

trigger.name: Redis cpu usage excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_CPU_HIGH}%]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis cpu usage has increased above {$REDIS_CPU_HIGH}% for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis cpu usage has decreased below {$REDIS_CPU_OK}% for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.expression: ({TRIGGER.VALUE}=0 and (({Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_last_save_time,].now()} - {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_last_save_time,].last()}) > {$REDIS_DB_SAVE_TIME} and {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_changes_since_last_save,].last()} > 0)) or ({TRIGGER.VALUE}=1 and (({Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_last_save_time,].now()} - {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_last_save_time,].last()}) > {$REDIS_DB_SAVE_TIME} and {Template Redis Server:redis.info[{$REDIS_SERVER},{$REDIS_PORT},{$REDIS_TIMEOUT},{$REDIS_PASSWORD},integer,persistence,rdb_changes_since_last_save,].last()} > 0))
trigger.name: Redis database has items to save and has not occured on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Last Save:{ITEM.VALUE1} Items:{ITEM.VALUE3}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis database has items to save and has not done so for {$REDIS_DB_SAVE_TIME} seconds and return to normal when the Redis database has no items to save.

trigger.name: Redis database last save not ok on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis database last save status is not ok and return to normal when the Redis database last save status is ok for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis evicted keys increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis keys evicted has increased and will return to normal when the Redis keys evicted remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis keyspace hit ratio too low on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_HIT_RATIO_HIGH}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis keyspace hit ratio has decreased below {$REDIS_HIT_RATIO_HIGH} for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis keyspace hit ratio has increased above {$REDIS_HIT_RATIO_OK} for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis keyspace misses increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis keyspace misses has increased and will return to normal when the Redis keyspace misses remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis master io has not occurred on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis master io has not occurred for {$REDIS_OK_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis master io has occurred.

trigger.name: Redis master link down on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis master link is down for{$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis master link is up for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis memory fragmentation excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_MEM_FRAG_HIGH}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis memory fragmentation has increased above {$REDIS_MEM_FRAG_HIGH} for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis memory fragmentation has decreased below {$REDIS_MEM_FRAG_OK} for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis port connection failed on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis server port is not connectable for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and return to normal when the Redis server port is connectable for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis port connection latency excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_CONN_LATENCY_HIGH}s]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis server port connection latency is greater than {$REDIS_CONN_LATENCY_HIGH} for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and return to normal when the Redis server port connection latency is below {$REDIS_CONN_LATENCY_OK} for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis server restarted on {$REDIS_SERVER}
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis restarts and is detected if the up time in seconds decreases.

trigger.name: Redis session creation failed on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis session creation status is unsuccessful for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and return to normal when the Redis server session creation status is successful for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis session creation latency excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_SESS_LATENCY_HIGH}s]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis session creation latency is greater than {$REDIS_SESS_LATENCY_HIGH} for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and return to normal when the Redis session creation latency is less than {$REDIS_SESS_LATENCY_OK} for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis slave count decreased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis slave count has decreased and will return to normal when the Redis slave count remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis slave count increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis slave count has increased and will return to normal when the Redis slave count remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis slowlog length increased on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Current:{ITEM.VALUE1} Previous:{ITEM.VALUE2}]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis slowlog length has increased and will return to normal when the Redis slowlog length remains constant for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.

trigger.name: Redis virtual memory usage excessive on {$REDIS_SERVER} [Value:{ITEM.VALUE1} Threshold:{$REDIS_MEM_VIRT_HIGH}b]
trigger.description: This trigger will fire when the Redis cpu usage has increased above {$REDIS_MEM_VIRT_HIGH} bytes for {$REDIS_HIGH_TIME} and will return to normal when the Redis cpu usage has decreased below {$REDIS_MEM_VIRT_OK} bytes for {$REDIS_OK_TIME}.
